<div type="definition">
<p>UNTRUE so that one is INTENSELY NOT ABLE to IMAGINE it to be TRUE.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current word for contradictory absurdity is bèi 悖.</p>
<p>2. Huāng 荒 focusses on the confusion more than the contradictoriness.</p>
<p>3. Dàn 誕 focusses on the loquaciousness of absurd discourse.</p>
<p>4. Guāi miù 乖謬 focusses on the misguidedness which is the result of incoherence.</p></div></div>
